'''Stratford University''' is a private, [[higher education]]al institution founded in 1976. Stratford specializes in [[adult education]] and offers placement assistance for students and graduates. It delivers [[Online education|online]], [[classroom]], and [[blended learning|blended online/classroom]] programs.<ref name="Stratford Catalog">{{cite web | title=Stratford University 2010-11 Catalog | url=http://www.stratford.edu/img/fckimages/2010-11Catalogweb.pdf | accessdate=2010-03-24}}</ref>

Stratford is a wholly owned subsidiary of The American Transportation Institute, Inc., a privately held Virginia corporation. Stratford has campuses in Virginia ([[Falls Church, Virginia|Falls Church]], [[Woodbridge, Virginia|Woodbridge]],<ref>{{cite web | title=Stratford University opens Woodbridge campus | url=http://www2.insidenova.com/isn/news/local/article/stratford_university_opens_woodbridge_campus/30640/ | accessdate=2010-03-15}}</ref> and [[Richmond, Virginia|Richmond]]<ref>{{cite web | title=Stratford University to Enter Richmond Market | url=http://www.thalhimer.com/news/item/stratford_university_to_enter_richmond_market/ | accessdate=2010-03-15}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Stratford University's Glen Allen Campus Creates 150 Jobs|url=http://www.wtvr.com/wtvr-stratford-universitys-glen-allen-campus-creates-150-jobs-20110406,0,1373575.story?track=rss|accessdate=20 April 2011}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=GRACRE honors Richmond's top real estate projects|url=http://www2.timesdispatch.com/business/business/2011/mar/31/TDBIZ03-gracre-honors-richmonds-top-real-estate-pr-ar-939779/|accessdate=20 April 2011}}</ref>), 
as well as [[New Delhi|New Delhi, India]],.<ref>{{cite web | title=Stratford University to set up campus in India | url=http://www.indianexpress.com/news/stratford-university-to-set-up-campus-in-ind/528941/ | accessdate=2010-03-15}}</ref> The majority of the student body is non-traditional and works full-time while attending school. Stratford's [[international student]] body is diverse and represents over thirty countries.<ref name="International Booklet">{{cite web | title=Stratford University International Student Booklet | url=http://www.stratford.edu/img/fckimages/International%20Student%20Booklet.pdf| accessdate=2010-03-22}}</ref>

Stratford has partnered with the [[Global Land Coalition]] to provide distance education services in developing countries and with the K. K. Modi Group to offer residential American degrees in India.<ref>{{cite web | title=Stratford University Opens Campus in India | url=http://www.theepochtimes.com/n2/content/view/23472/ | accessdate=2010-03-15}}</ref>

Dr. Richard R. Shurtz II, Stratford president, won the 2009 [[Ernst & Young]] Entrepreneur Of The Year award in Greater Washington for the Government/Education Services category.<ref>{{cite web | title=Winners for Ernst & Young Entrepreneur Of The Year 2009 awards in Greater Washington Announced | url=http://www.ey.com/US/en/Newsroom/News-releases/Winners-for-Ernst---Young-Entrepreneur-Of-The-Year-2009-awards-in-Greater-Washington-announced | accessdate=2010-03-15}}</ref><ref>{{cite web | title=Ex-Techie Gets Educational | url=http://www.bisnow.com/washington_dc_tech_news_story.php?p=5375| accessdate=2010-03-16}}</ref> Stratford University was ranked as one of the ''Top 100 Graduate Degree Producers for All Disciplines'' in 2009 by Diverse Education.<ref>"Top Graduate Degree Producers", ''Diverse Issues in Higher Education'', July 23, 2009.</ref><ref>{{cite web | title=Top 100 - Graduate Degree Producers | url=http://diverseeducation.com/article/12744/ | accessdate=2010-03-23}}</ref>

The [[U.S. Immigration and Customs Enforcement]] (ICE) agency and [[Computerworld]] reported that the Stratford University has a larger number of [[F-1 visa|F-1 Visa]] students receiving post-graduate [[Optional Practical Training]] (OPT) [[STEM fields|STEM]] extensions (727) than any other school in the US, with twice the combined total of the entire [[Ivy League]] <U+2014> Brown (26), Columbia (105), Cornell (90), Dartmouth (18), Harvard (27), Princeton (16), Penn (50), and Yale (9).<ref>{{cite web | title=Computerword: How the Tech Worker Visa is Remaking IT in America | url=http://www.computerworld.com/s/article/9196738/H_1B_at_20_How_the_tech_worker_visa_is_remaking_IT_in_America?taxonomyId=10&pageNumber=2 | accessdate=2010-11-23}}</ref><ref>{{cite web | title=ICE Data: All OPT Extension Requests for F-1 students with a STEM Primary Major | url=http://public.tableausoftware.com/views/OPT_EXT_STEM_MAJOR/Schools?:embed=yes&:toolbar=yes | accessdate=2010-11-23}}</ref><ref>{{cite web | title= Slashdot: How the Tech Worker Visa Is Remaking IT in America | url=http://news.slashdot.org/story/10/11/21/2243234/How-the-Tech-Worker-Visa-Is-Remaking-IT-In-America?from=rss | accessdate=2010-11-29}}</ref>

==Academic programs==
'''Stratford University''' awards [[Postgraduate education|graduate]] and [[undergraduate]] degrees in a number of disciplines including [[business administration]], [[computer information systems]], [[health sciences]], [[nursing]], [[culinary arts]], and [[hotel management]]. Online, residential, and blended programs are available. All online and blended courses use the Stratford online [[Moodle]] platform hosted in Stratford's data center.<ref>{{cite web | title=Stratford University Online Programs | url=http://www.stratford.edu/stratford-university/online-programs | accessdate=24 May 2010}}</ref> The learning outcomes embedded within the curriculum are employer-centric, while the teaching methods and delivery style are student-centric.

The University offers accelerated degree programs for those who wish to start their careers quickly. An associate's degree can be earned in 15 months, a bachelor's degree in 30 months, and a master's degree in 15 months. The table below lists all programs and indicates which are available online.<ref>{{cite web |title=Stratford University Academic Programs  | url=http://www.stratford.edu/stratford-university/academic-programs | accessdate=2010-03-22}}</ref>

